This paper deals with the analysis of mobile phone communication patterns and social network graphs to infer users' socio-economic attributes such as their income level. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks), followed by cs.SOC (Social and Behavioral Sciences), cs.CYBER (Cybersecurity and Privacy), cs.CR (Cryptography and Security), and cs.DB (Databases).
